<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1438,152,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">
<materialsCitation country="Gabon" county="Monts de Cristal National Park" location="Monte Alen National Park" municipality="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" specimenCount="2">
These three collections from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E787FD154EC5666ED8962789E129C1:8E9160301548C5666FBA90F68B432BDB" box="[501,820,152,178]" country="Gabon" county="Monts de Cristal National Park" municipality="The" name="Monte Alen National Park" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Monte Alen National Park</location>
, Rio Muni, are the first records since Gustav Mann collected the 
<typeStatus box="[308,358,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
in 
<quantity box="[397,486,190,216]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.72948" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" unit="in" value="1862.0">1862 in</quantity>
the “Sierra del Crystal”. The 
<typeStatus box="[838,889,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
locality is generally supposed to be in 
<collectingCountry box="[1350,1431,190,216]" name="Gabon" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, but could equally be in 
<collectingCountry box="[455,576,229,255]" name="Equatorial Guinea" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Rio Muni</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[594,834,229,255]" name="Equatorial Guinea" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Equatorial Guinea</collectingCountry>
), since the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E787FD154EC5666ED8962789E129C1:8E9160301548C5666D9C908B8CCA2B96" box="[979,1213,229,255]" country="Gabon" county="Monts de Cristal National Park" municipality="The" name="Crystal Mountains" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Crystal Mountains</location>
spread over both countries, and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E787FD154EC5666ED8962789E129C1:8E9160301548C5666F0C916289EC2A4F" box="[323,411,268,294]" country="Gabon" county="Monts de Cristal National Park" municipality="The" name="Mann's" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Mann’s</location>
itinerary is not precisely known. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E787FD154EC5666ED8962789E129C1:8E9160301548C5666D6B91628B322A4F" box="[804,837,268,294]" country="Gabon" county="Monts de Cristal National Park" municipality="The" name="As" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">As</location>
there are no further records of 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1312,268,294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mannii">
<emphasis box="[1203,1312,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">T. mannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1350,1431,268,294]" name="Gabon" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, its occurence in the country needs confirmation, although it is quite likely. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1043,1088,306,332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">The</collectingMunicipality>
species should be looked for on inselbergs, especially in the 
<collectingCounty box="[518,886,345,371]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Monts de Cristal National Park</collectingCounty>
, parts of which are difficult to access
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1438,152,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">
A collection from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[528,606,384,410]" name="Gabon" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Gabon</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[625,875,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Wieringa et al. 5033,</emphasis>
WAG) cited with doubt under 
<taxonomicName box="[1248,1359,384,410]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mannii">
<emphasis box="[1248,1359,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">T. mannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the checklist of Gabonese vascular plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Sosef, M. S. M. &amp; Wieringa, J. J. &amp; Jongkind, C. C. H. &amp; Achoundong, G. &amp; Azizet Issembe, Y. &amp; Bedigian, D. &amp; van den Berg, R. G. &amp; Breteler, F. J. &amp; Cheek, M. &amp; Degreef, J. &amp; Faden, R. B. &amp; Goldblatt, P. &amp; van der Maesen, L. J. G. &amp; Ngok Banak, L. &amp; Niangadouma, R. &amp; Nzabi, T. &amp; Nziengui, B. &amp; Rogers, Z. S. &amp; Stevart, T. &amp; van Valkenburg, J. L. C. H. &amp; Walters, G. &amp; de Wilde, J. J. F. E." box="[618,827,422,448]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 438" refId="ref4311" refString="Sosef, M. S. M., Wieringa, J. J., Jongkind, C. C. H., Achoundong, G., Azizet Issembe, Y., Bedigian, D., van den Berg, R. G., Breteler, F. J., Cheek, M., Degreef, J., Faden, R. B., Goldblatt, P., van der Maesen, L. J. G., Ngok Banak, L., Niangadouma, R., Nzabi, T., Nziengui, B., Rogers, Z. S., Stevart, T., van Valkenburg, J. L. C. H., Walters, G., de Wilde, J. J. F. E. (2006) Check-list des plantes vasculaires du Gabon. Checklist of Gabonese vascular plants. Scripta Botanica Belgica 35: 1 - 438." type="journal article" year="2006">
Sosef 
<emphasis box="[695,755,422,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
), is definitely not this species (it has much smaller flowers and differently shaped leaves). However, it remains unidentified for now, having some characters of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Chamisso &amp; Schlechtendahl" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[210,345,500,526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thouarsii">
<emphasis box="[210,345,500,526]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">T. thouarsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engler" authorityYear="1922" box="[402,539,500,526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dinklagei">
<emphasis box="[402,539,500,526]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">T. dinklagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1438,152,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">
The flower colour of 
<taxonomicName box="[448,557,538,564]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mannii">
<emphasis box="[448,557,538,564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">T. mannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded by 
<emphasis box="[737,1046,538,564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">Parmentier &amp; Esono 2970</emphasis>
as mauve, with two white stripes on the lower lip. The label of the 
<typeStatus box="[542,593,577,603]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
specimen just states “corolla purple”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1438,152,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">
The species grows in fringing forest on inselbergs, at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[1026,1193,616,642]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.115" metricValueMax="1.13" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" unit="m" value="1115.0" valueMax="1130.0" valueMin="1100.0">1100–1130 m</quantity>
, a habitat where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engler" authorityYear="1922" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dinklagei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="44">T. dinklagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs.
</paragraph>
